
[1]perspicuous

   PERSPIC'UOUS, a. [L.perspicuus.]

   Transparent; translucent. [Little used.]

   1. Clear to the understanding; that may be clearly understood; not
   obscure or ambiguous. Language is perspicuous when it readily presents
   to the reader or hearer the precise ideas which are intended to be
   expressed. Meaning, sense or signification if perspicuous, when it is
   clearly and easily comprehended.
